'[`0e16df2`](https://github.com/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pull/366/commits/0e16df26ece1ce9dc472e2c334e97fb818c13c6b)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 14, 34, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'atharva-18', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 674903967, 'comment_body': 'what do you think about creating here a enum, instead of this string ? It looks weird', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 22, 15, 13, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ahcorde', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 674946594, 'comment_body': 'The value of `_xyzExpressedIn` is `__model__` whenever the joint axis vector is expressed in the parent frame. How about a boolean value, for example, `useParentFrame` that is set to true whenever the joint axis vector is expressed in the parent frame? Using `_xyzExpressedIn` as a string looks more verbose, however.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 22, 16, 0, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'atharva-18', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 685402088, 'comment_body': '@iche033 thoughts?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 9, 17, 52, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ahcorde', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 685542833, 'comment_body': "I think using the string `_model_` can be tricky. We can have joints connecting two different models and also nested models. Ign-rendering also doesn't have the concept of a 'model' as it's just a scene tree with nodes in hierarchical structure.  The current implementation looks like it's relative to its parent so I think a bool `useParentFrame`  fits better.

An alternative option is to take the name or id of a node as an argument. The function then creates the axis relative to that node. ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 9, 21, 45, 43, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'iche033', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688416834, 'comment_body': 'friendly ping @atharva-18 ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 13, 10, 38, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ahcorde', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688447781, 'comment_body': "> I think using the string `_model_` can be tricky. We can have joints connecting two different models and also nested models. Ign-rendering also doesn't have the concept of a 'model' as it's just a scene tree with nodes in hierarchical structure. The current implementation looks like it's relative to its parent so I think a bool `useParentFrame` fits better.
> 
> An alternative option is to take the name or id of a node as an argument. The function then creates the axis relative to that node.

